 [[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]], [[1999-2000 Scottish Premier League|Premier League]], 16 October 1999 \n|lowest attendance=5,584 v Alloa Athletic, [[1999-2000 Scottish Cup|Scottish Cup]], 5 February 2000\n|average attendance=9,419 \n|pattern_la1=_whiteshoulders\n|pattern_b1=_whitestripes4\n|pattern_ra1=_whiteshoulders\n|pattern_sh1=_bluesides\n|leftarm1=0000ff\n|body1=0000ff\n|rightarm1=0000ff\n|shorts1=\n|socks1=\n|pattern_la2=_blacklower\n|pattern_b2=_thinblacksides\n|pattern_ra2=_blacklower\n|pattern_sh2=_whitesides\n|pattern_so2=_4_hoops_thin_burgundy\n|leftarm2=660000\n|body2=660000\n|rightarm2=660000\n|shorts2=000000\n|socks2=\n|prevseason=[[1998\u201399 Kilmarnock F.C. season|1998\u201399]]\n|nextseason=[[2000\u201301 Kilmarnock F.C. season|2000\u201301]]\n}}\n\nThe [[1999\u20132000 in Scottish football|1999\u20132000 season]] was [[Kilmarnock F.C.|Kilmarnock's]] second season in the [[1999\u20132000 Scottish Premier League|Scottish Premier League]]. Kilmarnock also competed in the [[1999\u20132000 Scottish Cup|Scottish Cup]], [[1999\u20132000 Scottish League Cup|Scottish League Cup]] and the [[1999\u20132000 UEFA Cup|UEFA Cup]].\n\n\n\n==Summary==\n\n\n===Season===\nKilmarnock finished ninth in the [[1999\u20132000 Scottish Premier League|Scottish Premier League]] with 37 points. They reached the semi\u2013final of the [[Scottish League Cup|League Cup]], losing to [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]].<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.londonhearts.com/scores/a2000/kilmarnock2000.htm | title=Results for Kilmarnock for 1999\u201300 | publisher=londonhearts.com | accessdate=16 April 2020}}</ref> Kilmarnock also reached the third round of the [[Scottish Cup]], losing to [[Alloa Athletic F.C.|Alloa Athletic]]<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.londonhearts.com/scores/a2000/kilmarnock2000.htm | title=Results for Kilmarnock for 1999\u201300 | publisher=londonhearts.com | accessdate=16 April 2020}}</ref> and lost in the first round of the [[1999\u20132000 UEFA Cup|UEFA Cup]] to [[1. FC Kaiserslautern|1. FC Kaiserslautern]].<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.worldfootball.net/report/europa-league-1999-2000-1-runde-kilmarnock-fc-1-fc-kaiserslautern/ | title=Kilmarnock 0 2 1. FC Kaiserslautern | publisher=worldfootball.net | accessdate=16 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n\n==Results and fixtures==\n\n''Kilmarnock's score comes first''\n\n{{legend2|#CCFFCC|Win|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#FFFFCC|Draw|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#FFCCCC|Loss|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#CCCCCC|Postponed|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n\n\n===Scottish Premier League===\n{{Main article|1999\u20132000 Scottish Premier League}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:100%; text-align:center\"\n!Match!!Date!!Opponent!!Venue!!Result!!Attendance!!Scorers\n|-style=\"background: #FFCCCC;\"\n|1||31 July 1999||[[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]]||A||1\u20132||48,074||[[Ally Mitchell|Mitchell]] 65'\n|-style=\"background: #CCFFCC;\"\n|2||7 August 1999||[[Aberdeen F.C.|Aberdeen]]||H||2\u20130||8,378||[[Garry Hay|Hay]] 38', 62'\n|-style=\"background: #FFCCCC;\"\n|3||15 August 1999||[[St Johnstone F.C.|St Johnstone]]||A||0\u20132||4,681||\n|-style=\"background: #FFCCCC;\"\n|4||21 August 1999||[[Motherwell F.C.|Motherwell]]||H||0\u20131||7,732||\n|-style=\"background: #FFFFCC;\"\n|5||29 August 1999||[[Dundee United F.C.|Dundee United]]||A||0\u20130||6,621||\n|-style=\"background: #FFCCCC;\"\n|6||12 September 1999||[[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]]||H||0\u20131||14,328||\n|-style=\"background: #CCFFCC;\"\n|7||19 September 1999||[[Hibernian F.C.|Hibernian]]||A||3\u20130||11,337||[[Mark Reilly|Reilly]] 12', [[Mike Jeffrey|Jeffrey]] 80', [[Ally McCoist|McCoist]] 90'\n|-style=\"background: #FFCCCC;\"\n|8||25 September 1999||[[Dundee F.C.|Dundee]]||H||0\u20132||7,433||\n|-style=\"background: #FFFFCC;\"\n|9||16 October 1999||[[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]]||H||1\u20131||15,795||[[Mike Jeffrey|Jeffrey]] 73'\n|-style=\"background: #FFFFCC;\"\n|10||23 October 1999||[[Aberdeen F.C.|Aberdeen]]||A||2\u20132||1